In Decipad you can concatenate two compatible tables using the `concatenate` function. These tables need to have the same column names and each corresponding column needs to have the same type of values.

```
TableA = {
  ColA = [1, 2, 3]
  ColB = [true, false, true]
}

TableB = {
  ColA = [4, 5, 6]
  ColB = [false, true, false]
}

concatenate(TableA, TableB)
```

will yield

```
{
  ColA = [ 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 ],
  ColB = [ true, false, true, false, true, false ]
}
```
